reviewText:
This video is the same style as any other video. Click the camera is in the video, and of course an oh so Diego dilemma. Diego embarks on a journey to find a missing whirly gig beetle dance partner. On the way there is use of Spanish language and some fun bug info on a whirly gig beetle. Apparently if they get into trouble they can release omit a foul odor with the command "stinky smell" lol.

Okay enough of the cuteness. Bottom line this video is actually tolerable to watch or let play in the background over and over. I have no problems playing this video on any device that I own. Dvd player, mini dvd player or PS2.
My son loves Go Diego Go!  He has watched this DVD so many times he knows what is going to happen next!  He is 2.5 yrs.
My one year old boiy loves Diego and he has learn so much from these cartoon that I recommend it to every one.
I can't rate this b/c I bought it used and it wouldn't play. But the seller did send me a new one (I had to chose a different video because they didnt' have any more copies of bug world.
My 19 month old son loves Diego. He watched this the last hour of a 7 hour trip. He loved it!
This DVD arrived on time and is just like new.  Is a great DVD for my Grandson.
What child doesn't love the heroic Diego?  Great introduction to saving the environment, saving animals, and the Spanish language!  Perfect for toddlers and young kids!
My grandson loves this
If the recipient of the DVD is a fan of Diego, he/she will enjoy watching it.

This DVD is very nice for Children's.  My grandsons love it.  It teaches them to take care of the animals.

I bought this for my niece and she watched it over and over again.  I got it used but there were no scratches and the DVD played with no problems and was the right price.

4 episodes on this DVD are:
It's a Bugs World
Diego the Hero
Alicia and Whitetail to the rescue
Whistling Willie finds a buddy
